TITLE Garden Vegetable Crustless Quiche

# Preheat oven to 400F.
# In a large bowl beat [8 item eggs] until fluffy.
# Add [3 oz [shredded] extra sharp cheddar cheese], [3 oz [shredded] monterey jack cheese], [1/2 cup milk], [1/2 cup all purpose flour], [1 tsp baking powder], [1/2 tsp salt], and [16 oz cottage cheese],
# In a large skillet saute [4 cup [sliced] zucchini], [1 cup [finely chopped] red bell pepper], and [8 oz spinach] until tender. Cool sauted vegetables slightly.
# Add sauted vegetables and [1/2 cup [chopped] parsley] to the egg mixture.
# Pour mixture into a lightly oiled 3-quart casserole dish.
# Top with [3 oz [shredded] extra sharp cheddar cheese] and [3 oz [shredded] monterey jack cheese]
# Slice [2 item tomato] and arrange over cheese.
# Bake at 400F for 15 minutes.
# Reduce oven temperature to 350F and bake until lightly browned and set.
